cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.CE, cs.CL

This paper deals with the problem of multilabel classification in the context of gene function prediction using a hierarchical categorization scheme. The proposed methods involve incorporating information about the hierarchy to improve prediction accuracy. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), databases (cs.DB), computational biology (cs.CE), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, given that the focus is on developing and comparing different machine learning approaches, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
